The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code calls strlen(url) without any validation that 'url' is non-NULL and points to a NUL-terminated character array. If the caller/library were to pass a NULL pointer or a buffer that is not terminated with '\0' (for example a truncated or malformed URL), strlen will read past the object bounds and cause an out-of-bounds access (buffer over-read). This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>
